President Obama has announced the redesign of the Transition Assistance Program, which will help servicemembers transition to civilian life. The new program, called Transition GPS, will extend the program period from 3 days to 5-7 days and provide stronger counseling and guidance. It will also transform the military's approach to education and training for servicemembers. Additionally, President Obama called on Congress to pass his Veterans Job Corps proposal and extend tax credits for businesses that hire veterans. The article also highlights other initiatives by the Obama Administration to support veterans and military families, such as increasing access to reemployment services, developing online tools for veteran employment, and strengthening the VA.